muros (0.9.10) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Gateway monitoring now functional on Debian. The gateway-monitoring path
    (dpinger.inc, gateway_status.php, gateway_watcher.php) and the monitor host
    route (system_host_route via iproute2) were already OS-independent; the only
    missing piece was the daemon. dpinger 3.6 is now packaged for Debian 13 and
    pulled in as a dependency, so per-gateway latency, loss and availability
    monitoring (the basis for multi-WAN failover) work out of the box.
  * Add dpinger to Depends (served from the MurOS apt repository).

 -- MurOS <dev@muros.org>  Sat, 20 Jun 2026 11:35:00 +0000

muros (0.9.9) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix login HTTP 500 (surfaced in the browser as a CSRF error): the package
    now ships the vendored contrib/ libraries to /usr/local/opnsense/contrib.
    The auth factory enumerates every connector at login and the TOTP
    connector requires base32/Base32.php, which was missing.
  * Appliance boot robustness: interface units no longer order after
    network-online.target (they bring the network up), avoiding a long
    wait-online delay; interface assignment runs before interface addressing.

 -- MurOS <dev@muros.org>  Sat, 20 Jun 2026 10:40:00 +0200

muros (0.9.8) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Ship 99-muros.ini (fpm+cli): include_path and appliance PHP limits so the
    MVC stack and .inc libraries resolve (fixes web UI HTTP 500).

 -- MurOS <dev@muros.org>  Sat, 20 Jun 2026 09:15:00 +0200

muros (0.9.7) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Web UI works out of the box: ship MurOS lighttpd config via a systemd
    drop-in, generate a self-signed certificate, seed a default config.xml.
  * Data-plane units (interfaces, firewall, interface-assign) shipped disabled
    so a fresh install never drops the management link.

 -- MurOS <dev@muros.org>  Sat, 20 Jun 2026 09:05:00 +0200

muros (0.9.6) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fork (OPNsense-on-Debian) supersedes the legacy FastAPI product.
  * System config now owned by the package: php-fpm pool (no more
    silent reset to max_children=5) and sysctl forwarding.
  * auth: port local account synchronization to Debian tooling (getent,
    userdel/groupdel, root/nogroup groups) instead of FreeBSD pw.
  * themes: restyle the sidebar header (left-aligned logo, version label,
    compact user and logout row).

 -- MurOS <dev@muros.org>  Fri, 19 Jun 2026 21:15:00 +0200

